(14, 'terms-conditions', 'Terms & Conditions', '<p class=\"copy\">The following terms and conditions constitute a valid and binding agreement between you and advisorzaroorihai.com (the â€œWebsiteâ€). By using the Website, and/or by registering with us, you signify that you agree to these terms and conditions, including that you consent to the Privacy Policy, which is incorporated herein by reference, and that you are agree to comply with applicable laws of India</p><p class=\"small-title\">I. DISCLAIMER</p><p class=\"copy\"> 1.1. Please note that we offer the information on the Website on an \"As is\" basisand the Website disclaims all warranties, either express or implied, including but not limited to the warranties of suitability and fitness of the Services for a particular purpose.</p><p class=\"copy\"> 1.2. The Website will not be responsible for any damage or loss of any kind direct, indirect, incidental, punitive and consequential arising from the use of or inability to use the Website, or any third-party link or services, or any material appearing on the Website. The contents of this Website are meant to inform the reader about the general information related to financial products and services. They are not intended to be, nor is, a form of publicity, advertisement or solicitation of work. The information should not be construed as providing financial advisory to the Customers.</p><p class=\"copy\"> 1.3. The links to other websites or resources are only for the informational purposes. The firm does not take any responsibility for the material or information sourced by the viewer from the links provided.</p><p class=\"copy\"> 1.4. The specific method, features and Services offered on the Website may be altered, improved, removed or adapted at any time by theWebsite at its sole discretion and without any notice. If you do not agree with any of these terms, do not use this Website.</p><p class=\"small-title\">II. ABOUT THE WEBSITE</p><p class=\"copy\"> 2.1. We are independent third-party enablers who have built a platform where the Customers can communicate with, and if the need be, meet the advisors. The Website has no control over the Services provided by the advisors. The Website is no way, directly or indirectly responsible for the advice and assistance provided by the advisors. The Website will not be responsible in case of any issues/discrepancies with the Services provided by the advisors.If you use the Services, you are solely responsible for communications posted by you or through your Account.</p><p class=\"copy\"> 2.2. All information provided on the Website is on a volunteer basis by the empanelled advisors as requested by the Customers on the Website. Each Customer and advisor has a varying level of knowledge. The Website in no manner certifies the accuracy of any information or level expertise relevant to any information exchanged on the Website.We do not certify or endorse any of the content on this Website, including without limitation any opinion, recommendation, advice, or any other information exchanged through the Website.</p><p class=\"copy\"> 2.3. The Website has multiple advisors empanelled for the same practice area and there might be instances wherein a similar question has been answered in two different ways by the advisor(s). The Website takes no liability towards these different opinions and answers of the advisors and encourages you to take another opinion from â€˜yourâ€™ advisor/ alternately decide which opinion to go ahead with based on merits and logical conclusions.</p><p class=\"small-title\">III. USER ACCOUNT/ADVISOR ACCOUNT</p><p class=\"copy\"> 3.1. You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of the password that you choose to access and use the Website (\'Account\'). Subject to applicable law, you agree to be liable for all uses of your Account whether or not actually authorized by you, including but not limited to uses of your Account to submit questions at the Website or to answer questions through the Website. This means that you should not supply your password to anyone who is not authorized to take actions for you.</p><p class=\"small-title\">IV. CONSEQUENCES OF BREACH</p><p class=\"copy\">4.1. We may immediately issue a warning (not necessarily always, sometime even without a notice), temporarily suspend, indefinitely suspend or terminate your membership, any of your current auctions, and any other information you place on the Website if you breach this agreement or if we are unable to verify or authenticate any information you provide to us.</p><p class=\"small-title\">V. ADVISOR OBLIGATIONS</p><p class=\"copy\">5.1. Advisors who are registered with the Website implicitly agree to pay a service charge, as per the revenue sharing agreement, for each Service that they opt to provide to the Customer who approach and make their payment to the advisors through the Website.</p><p class=\"copy\">5.2. Advisors who are registered with the Website implicitly agree to not solicit the Customers that they get connected to through the Website and to provide the Services through the Account created on the Website.</p><p class=\"copy\">5.3. If the advisor does not provide the Service opted by the Customer within the stipulated date mentioned in our Website or the date provided by the advisor himself, and if the advisor has not reverted to the email sent to by the Website and the Customer, in such case the Customer can claim for refund by sending an e-mail request along with the proof of email sent to the advisor. In such situation the advisor cannot deny the refund.</p><p class=\"copy\">5.4. The Website doesn\'t tolerate any misbehavior with the Customer while providing consultation.If the Customer complains of any misbehavior from the part of the advisor along with valid proof the Customer will be provided refund by the particular advisor and the advisor cannot claim his/her consultation fees.</p><p class=\"small-title\">VI. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY</p><p class=\"copy\"> 6.1. The opinions, statements, answers (collectively â€œConsultationâ€) provided by the advisors via the Websiteare solely the individual and independent opinions and statements of such individuals and do not reflect the opinions of the Website, its affiliates or any other organizations or institutions to which such advisor or such specialist or professional is affiliated or provides services. The Website will, not in any circumstance, be responsible or liable to pay for any damages, losses suffered by the Customers based on the Consultations received from the advisors.</p><p class=\"copy\"> 6.2. Theadvisors who participate in the Websiteare not employed by or agents of the Website. Although the Website does require advisors to provide basic information about themselves to the Website (for example, qualification proofs, number of years of experience etc.), and although the Website does rely upon and pass on this information to the Customers for their use, the Website does not separately verify this information and makes no representations as to the qualifications of any advisors. You are encouraged to investigate or perform your own due diligence concerning the advisors and their qualifications.</p><p class=\"small-title\">VII. EXCLUSION OF WARRANTIES:</p><ul class=\"bullets\"><p>7.1. The Website, in particular, does not warranty the following:</p><li>(a) Your use of the Services will meet your requirements,</li><li>(b) Your use of the Services will be uninterrupted, timely, secure or free from error,</li><li>(c) Any information obtained by you as a result of your use of the Services will be accurate or reliable, and</li><li>(d) That defects in the operation or functionality of any software provided to you as part of the Services will be corrected.</li><li>(e) No advice or information, whether oral or written, obtained by you from the Website or through or from the Services shall create any warranty not expressly stated in the terms.</li></ul><p class=\"small-title\">VIII. ASSIGNMENT</p><p class=\"copy\">8.1. We may assign this contract at any time to any parent, subsidiary, or any affiliated company, or as part of the sale to, merger with, or other transfer of our company to another entity. We will post a notice on the Website regarding any change of ownership so that you have the opportunity to discontinue your use of the Website or cancel your registration if you do not wish to continue to use the Website and the Services under the new ownership. You may not assign, transfer or sublicense this Agreement to anyone else and any attempt to do so in violation of this section shall be null and void.</p><p class=\"small-title\">IX. JURIDICTION</p><p class=\"copy\">9.1. Any dispute, questions, difference arising out of this agreement shall be settled as per the laws applicable in India. The courts in Mumbai shall have exclusive jurisdiction. All the costs of such litigation will be borne by the users of this Website.</p>'),
(15, 'privacy-policy', 'Privacy Policy', '<p class=\"copy\">This Privacy Policy applies to all the visitors of advisorzaroorihai.com (â€œWebsiteâ€). By visiting and/or using our Website, you agree to this Privacy Policy. Please read this privacy policy carefully. this privacy policy describes the way advisor zaroori hai and its affiliates (â€œweâ€, â€œusâ€ ourâ€) collect, process, handle, store, secure and use your personal information. throughout this privacy policy, â€œyouâ€ refers to the customer. you accept this privacy policy by visiting our website and/or through availing any of our services.</p><p class=\"copy\"> For the purposes of this Privacy Policy, â€œPersonal Informationâ€ shall mean any information that identifies or can be used to identify, contact or locate the person, to whom such information pertains, including, but not limited to, name, address, date of birth, phone number, fax number, email address, PAN, Aadhaar number, driving license/ passport/ voter identity card/ government issued identification card, financial profiles like the name of your employer, monthly salary, annual income, net worth, credit/ debit card details, details of your assets and liabilities, copies of identification documents, e-KYC, demographic information, photographs, biometric information, digital signature keys, bank account, card information and other Sensitive Personal Information.</p><p class=\"copy\"> â€œSensitive Personal Informationâ€ shall mean information relating to passwords, financial information such as Bank account or credit card or debit card orother payment instrument details, medical records and history, biometric information, any detail relating to the above clauses as provided to Us forproviding Service(s).</p><p class=\"copy\"> â€œServiceâ€ or â€œServicesâ€ shall mean the service provided by the Website to the Customers related to advisory. We are committed to keeping your Personal Information confidential and will only give it to others for the purposes set out in this Privacy Policy. Our Privacy Policy is regularly reviewed to make sure that we continue to serve your privacy interests. We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy and these changes will be posted on our Website. The date of last revision appears at the top and all changes take effect immediately upon posting.We will notify you of any material changes to this policy as required by law. We will also post an updated copy on Our Website. Please check Our Website periodically for updates.</p><p class=\"small-title\">1. Collection and Use of Personal Information</p><p class=\"copy\"> 1.1. When you use the Website, we collect, process, handle and store the Personal Information provided by you from time to time, in compliance with applicable laws. The primary aim in doing so is to provide you with a safe, efficient, and customized experience while using the Website, for providing of the Service(s) efficiently and to verify your identity and other information that you provide.</p><p class=\"copy\"> 1.2. We may use Google Analytics, a web analytics service provided by Google, Inc. Google Analytics uses first-party cookies to report on user interactions with Our web-based Services. These cookies store non-personally identifiable information. Google Analytics aggregates technical data (non-personally identifiable data relating to your usage of Our website) with data collected from Our other users. We use this information to identify the most popular areas of the Services and how to best present and customise them. We may use the unique identifier of your device for security purposes to track suspicious activity. For instance, if we detect that your account on advisorzaroorihai.com is accessed on multiple devices, we may contact you to ensure that you have authorized such access. Under no circumstance will your email address, password and any financial data be collected by or shared with Google Analytics.</p><p class=\"copy\"> 1.3. If you opt to open an account on the Website or use Our Service(s), you will be required to supply your Personal Information. Before permitting you to use the Services, we may require you to provide additional information, including but not limited to your date of birth, PAN, personal information stored with third parties such as social media sites (such as Facebook or Twitter) and other personal information. We may use this information to verify your identity or other information you provide</p><p class=\"copy\"> 1.4. The Personal Information provided by you will be solely used for purposes as laid down in tis Privacy Policy and shall be retained with Us for a period as permissible under the applicable laws or for the purposes as mentioned under this Privacy Policy.</p><p class=\"copy\"> 1.5. If you opt to open an account on the Website or use Our Service, you will be required to supply your Personal Information. Before permitting you to use the Services, we may require you to provide additional informationto verify your identity or other information you provide.</p><p class=\"copy\"> 1.6. We may occasionally ask you to complete optional online surveys. These surveys may ask you for contact information and demographic information (such as PIN code, age, or income level). We use this data to customize your experience on the Website, providing you with content that we think you might be interested in and by displaying content according to your preferences.</p><p class=\"copy\"> 1.7. We also collect information about you from third parties such as credit bureaus and other identity verification and fraud prevention services. This information we collect from such third-party sources is governed by your privacy policies agreed with those sources and with your express consent. By providing such third-party information by way of authorizing us to access such information, you agree that we may collect, store, process and share such information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.</p><p class=\"copy\"> 1.8. By providing your email and phone number to us, you are authorizing us, our representatives and Our partners to communicate with you through various modes like call, email to offer you Our Services opted by you, marketing material about solutions, promotional offers offered by Our partners. Irrespective of the fact that you have registered yourself under Do Not Disturb (â€œDNDâ€) or Do Not Call (â€œDNCâ€) service, you are still authorizing Us, Our representatives &amp;Our partners to communicate with you for the above mentioned purposes. There is no DNC check required for a number you leave on Our website or with Our agents. If you wish to opt-out receiving such communication from us you can do so by sending Us an e-mail at ______________.</p><p class=\"copy\"> 1.9. If you send Us personal correspondences, such as emails or letters, or if other users or third parties send Us correspondence about your activities or postings on the Website, we may collect such information into a file specific to you.</p><p class=\"copy\"> 1.10. If you telephone us we may also record and/or monitor calls for quality checks and staff training. Such recordings may also be used to help Us combat fraud.</p><p class=\"copy\"> 1.11. In the event that you want to review and/or update your information as provided to us, or obtain a copy of the same, please write to us at _______________.</p><p class=\"small-title\"> 2. Sharing of Personal Information</p><p class=\"copy\"> 2.1. We will keep your Personal Information confidential and only share it with others for the purposes explained in this Privacy Policy. We have trusted relationships with carefully selected banking and financial entities (to whom we provide service) or other third parties (who perform Services on Our behalf), some of which may be located within or outside of India. Examples of service providers we use are payment processors, email service providers and providers of hosting services. All service providers are required to maintain the security of your Personal Information and to use it only as permitted by Us and they must comply with the security practices and procedures as maintained by Us as set out in this Privacy Policy.</p><p class=\"copy\"> 2.2. Disclosure of Information. Under no circumstance will we sell or rent your Personal Information to anyone, for any reason, at any time. Our third party service providers are bound by the same standards of data security practices and procedures as we are under law and contract. They are subject to the same penalties as we are for the unauthorized disclosure of your personal information. However, under Indian law, Advisor Zaroori Hai remains liable to you, Our customer, for any unauthorised disclosure of your sensitive personal information.</p><ul class=\"bullets\"> <span>2.3. We may share your Personal Information:</span><li>(a) to transfer data, personal information etc. with any banking or financial entity or third party firm.</li><li>(b) to analyze usage of the Website or to improve the Service(s) as provided by Us.</li><li>(c) to send communications relevant to your use of Service(s)as offered by Us.</li><li>(d) in relation to research, to effectively control against error, fraud or other criminal activity.</li><li>(e) to enforce Our terms of use.</li><li>(f) to any person who has told Us and who we reasonably believe to be your parent, carer or helper where you are unable to handle your own affairs because of mental capacity or other similar issues.</li><li>(g) to any person to whom we sell or transfer (or enter into negotiations to sell or transfer) or with whom we merge Our business or any of Our rights or obligations under any agreement we may have with you. If the merger, transfer or sale consummates, the transferee or purchaser may use your Personal Information in the same way as Us.</li><li>(h) to regulators, ombudsmen or other authorities, including tax authorities, including those overseas, where we are requested by them to do so.</li><li></li><li></li><li></li><li></li><li></li><li></li><li></li></ul><p class=\"copy\">2.4. The Personal Information shared by you shall be used to perform background checks on your identity and your fitness to avail the Services offered by Us on the Website.</p><p class=\"copy\">2.5. If you click on one of the links to third party websites, you may be taken to websites we do not control. This policy does not apply to the privacy practices of those websites. Read the privacy policy of other websites carefully. We are not responsible for these third party sites.</p><p class=\"small-title\">3. Security Precautions</p><p class=\"copy\">3.1. Security measures (physical, electronic and managerial) are in place to protect you against the loss, misuse, and alteration of the Personal Information under Our control. We store Personal Information in encrypted form on computers and control access via secure web pages. We employ firewalls and other security technologies to protect Our servers from external attack. Access to the Websiteâ€™s server is restricted to authorized personnel and shared with employees strictly on a â€˜need to know basisâ€™. We shall also promptly notify you if any security breach is made known to Us in relation to unauthorized access to your Personal Information.</p><p class=\"copy\">3.2. Our security systems meet or exceed reasonable security standards and we are constantly monitoring internet developments to ensure Our systems evolve as required. However, while we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your Personal Information, no method of transmission over the Internet, or method of electronic storage, is 100% secure. Therefore, by using this Website, you agree that we will have no liability for disclosure of your Personal Information due to errors in transmission, infrastructure failures by Us or any intermediary (including telecom and internet service providers), or unauthorized acts of third parties.</p><p class=\"small-title\">4. Opting Out</p><p class=\"copy\">4.1. We will generally retain your Personal Information for as long as needed to provide you with details of Our Solutions and Services. If you change your mind, and donâ€™t wish to remain on Our contact list, just let Us know at ________________.</p><p class=\"copy\">4.2. As part of the application process, we ask you whether we may contact you about OurServices by telephone, post, email and SMS (or other reasonable method). If you ticked â€œyesâ€ but no longer wish to receive such communications, please contact Us on _____________.</p><p class=\"copy\">4.3. You have the right to withdraw your consent to Our use of your Personal Information at any time where we rely on your consent to use or process that information by sending an email to __________________. In such case, Advisor Zaroori Hai will unfortunately not be in a position to provide the Services to you.</p><p class=\"small-title\">5. Grievance Officer</p><p class=\"copy\">5.1. In accordance with the Information Technology Act, 2000 and the rules made thereunder, the name and contact details of the Grievance Officer are provided below in the event you have any questions or complaints regarding Our Privacy Policy or practices:</p><p class=\"copy\">Name: ____________________</p><p class=\"copy\">E-mail: ____________________</p><p class=\"copy\">Phone No.: ___________________________</p><p class=\"copy\">We are committed to providing a first response within 24 hours of receiving the complaint, and we aim to resolve all complaints within 3 (three) business days . Any delay in the resolution time shall be proactively communicated to you. If you do not hear back from us within a weekâ€™s time, please do write to Us at _________________ or escalation of your specific complaint to the relevant grievance redressal officer.</p><p class=\"small-title\">6. Our Legal Obligations</p><p class=\"copy\">6.1. This Privacy Policy is published on the Website in compliance with Regulation 4 of the (Indian) Information Technology (Reasonable Security Practices and Procedures and Sensitive Personal Information) Rules, 2011.</p><p class=\"copy\">6.2. We are bound by the (Indian) Information Technology Act, 2000, and comply with all its provisions available at http://deity.gov.in/content/it-act-2000-dpl-cyber-laws. Under Section 43A of the (Indian) Information Technology Act, 2000, advisorzaroorihai.com and all its service providers are obliged to maintain reasonable security procedures to safeguard your Personal Information.</p><p class=\"copy\">6.3. Under Regulation 5 of the Information Technology (Reasonable Security and Procedures and Sensitive Personal Data or Information) Rules, 2011, we are obliged to provide every Customer with a readable copy of the Personal Information you have provided Us. If you would like a copy, do get in touch with Us at _______________________.</p><p class=\"small-title\">7. Jurisdiction</p><p class=\"copy\">Any Dispute in relation to this Privacy Policy shall be governed by the laws of India and the courts in Mumbai shall have exclusive jurisdiction.</p>');

